gpt-4.5-preview.summary: Largest and most capable GPT model
gpt-4.5-preview.description: This is a research preview of GPT-4.5, our largest and most capable GPT model yet. Its deep world knowledge and better understanding of user intent makes it good at creative tasks and agentic planning. GPT-4.5 excels at tasks that benefit from creative, open-ended thinking and conversation, such as writing, learning, or exploring new ideas.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

gpt-4o.description: GPT-4o ("o" for "omni") is our versatile, high-intelligence flagship model. It accepts both text and image inputs and produces text outputs, including structured outputs. GPT-4o excels at tasks that benefit from creative, open-ended thinking and conversation, such as writing, learning, or exploring new ideas.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

o3-mini.description: o3-mini is our newest small reasoning model, providing high intelligence at the same cost and latency targets as o1-mini. It supports key developer features, including Structured Outputs, function calling, and Batch API. Designed for reasoning tasks, it processes text input and returns text output.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

o1.description: The o1 series of models are trained with reinforcement learning to perform complex reasoning. o1 models think before they answer, producing a long internal chain of thought before responding to the user.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

o1-mini.summary: A faster, more affordable reasoning model than o1
o1-mini.description: The o1 reasoning model is designed to solve hard problems across domains. o1-mini is a faster and more affordable reasoning model, but we recommend using the newer o3-mini model that features higher intelligence at the same latency and price as o1-mini.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

o1-pro.summary: A version of o1 with more compute for better responses
o1-pro.description: The o1 series of models are trained with reinforcement learning to think before they answer and perform complex reasoning. The o1-pro model uses more compute to think harder and provide consistently better answers. o1-pro is available in the Responses API only to enable support for multi-turn model interactions before responding to API requests, and other advanced API features in the future.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

gpt-4o-audio-preview.summary: GPT-4o models capable of audio inputs and outputs
gpt-4o-audio-preview.description: This is a preview release of the GPT-4o Audio models. These models accept audio inputs and outputs, and can be used in the Chat Completions REST API.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

chatgpt-4o-latest.description: ChatGPT-4o points to the GPT-4o snapshot currently used in ChatGPT. GPT-4o is our versatile, high-intelligence flagship model. It accepts both text and image inputs and produces text outputs (including Structured Outputs). It is the best model for most tasks and is our most capable model outside of our o-series models.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

gpt-4o-mini.summary: Fast, affordable small model for focused tasks
gpt-4o-mini.description: GPT-4o mini ("o" for "omni") is a fast, affordable small model for focused tasks. It accepts both text and image inputs and produces text outputs (including Structured Outputs). It is ideal for fine-tuning, and model outputs from a larger model like GPT-4o can be distilled to GPT-4o-mini to produce similar results at lower cost and latency.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

gpt-4o-mini-audio-preview.summary: Smaller model capable of audio inputs and outputs
gpt-4o-mini-audio-preview.description: This is a preview release of the smaller GPT-4o Audio mini model. It's designed to accept audio input or create audio outputs via the REST API.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

gpt-4o-realtime-preview.summary: Model capable of realtime text and audio inputs and outputs
gpt-4o-realtime-preview.description: This is a preview release of the GPT-4o Realtime model, capable of responding to audio and text inputs in realtime over WebRTC or a WebSocket interface.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

gpt-4o-mini-realtime-preview.summary: Smaller realtime model for text and audio inputs and outputs
gpt-4o-mini-realtime-preview.description: This is a preview release of the GPT-4o-mini Realtime model, capable of responding to audio and text inputs in realtime over WebRTC or a WebSocket interface.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

gpt-4-turbo.description: GPT-4 Turbo is the next generation of GPT-4, an older high-intelligence GPT model. It was designed to be a cheaper, better version of GPT-4. Today, we recommend using a newer model like GPT-4o.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

gpt-4.description: GPT-4 is an older version of a high-intelligence GPT model, usable in Chat Completions.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

gpt-3.5-turbo.summary: Legacy GPT model for cheaper chat and non-chat tasks
gpt-3.5-turbo.description: GPT-3.5 Turbo models can understand and generate natural language or code and have been optimized for chat using the Chat Completions API but work well for non-chat tasks as well. As of July 2024, use gpt-4o-mini in place of GPT-3.5 Turbo, as it is cheaper, more capable, multimodal, and just as fast. GPT-3.5 Turbo is still available for use in the API.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

dall-e-3.description: DALL·E is an AI system that creates realistic images and art from a natural language description. DALL·E 3 currently supports the ability, given a prompt, to create a new image with a specific size.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on image resolution per generated image. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

dall-e-2.description: DALL·E is an AI system that creates realistic images and art from a natural language description. Older than DALL·E 3, DALL·E 2 offers more control in prompting and more requests at once.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on image resolution per generated image. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

gpt-4o-mini-tts.summary: Text-to-speech model powered by GPT-4o mini
gpt-4o-mini-tts.description: GPT-4o mini TTS is a text-to-speech model built on GPT-4o mini, a fast and powerful language model. Use it to convert text to natural sounding spoken text. The maximum number of input tokens is 2000.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

tts-1.description: TTS is a model that converts text to natural sounding spoken text. The tts-1 model is optimized for realtime text-to-speech use cases. Use it with the Speech endpoint in the Audio API.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

tts-1-hd.description: TTS is a model that converts text to natural sounding spoken text. The tts-1-hd model is optimized for high quality text-to-speech use cases. Use it with the Speech endpoint in the Audio API.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

gpt-4o-transcribe.description: GPT-4o Transcribe is a speech-to-text model that uses GPT-4o to transcribe audio. It offers improvements to word error rate and better language recognition and accuracy compared to original Whisper models. Use it for more accurate transcripts.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

gpt-4o-mini-transcribe.summary: Speech-to-text model powered by GPT-4o mini
gpt-4o-mini-transcribe.description: GPT-4o mini Transcribe is a speech-to-text model that uses GPT-4o mini to transcribe audio. It offers improvements to word error rate and better language recognition and accuracy compared to original Whisper models. Use it for more accurate transcripts.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

whisper-1.description: Whisper is a general-purpose speech recognition model, trained on a large dataset of diverse audio. You can also use it as a multitask model to perform multilingual speech recognition as well as speech translation and language identification.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

text-embedding-3-small.description: text-embedding-3-small is our improved, more performant version of our ada embedding model. Embeddings are a numerical representation of text that can be used to measure the relatedness between two pieces of text. Embeddings are useful for search, clustering, recommendations, anomaly detection, and classification tasks.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

text-embedding-3-large.description: text-embedding-3-large is our most capable embedding model for both English and non-English tasks. Embeddings are a numerical representation of text that can be used to measure the relatedness between two pieces of text. Embeddings are useful for search, clustering, recommendations, anomaly detection, and classification tasks.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

text-embedding-ada-002.description: text-embedding-ada-002 is our improved, more performant version of our ada embedding model. Embeddings are a numerical representation of text that can be used to measure the relatedness between two pieces of text. Embeddings are useful for search, clustering, recommendations, anomaly detection, and classification tasks.

pricing.pricing_model: Pricing is based on the number of tokens used. For tool-specific models, like search and computer use, there's a fee per tool call.

omni-moderation-latest.summary: Identify potentially harmful content in text and images
omni-moderation-latest.description: Moderation models are free models designed to detect harmful content. This model is our most capable moderation model, accepting images as input as well.

pricing.pricing_model: Free

text-moderation-latest.description: Moderation models are free models designed to detect harmful content. This is our text-only moderation model; we expect omni-moderation-* models to be the best default moving forward.

pricing.pricing_model: Free

gpt-4o-search-preview.summary: GPT model for web search in Chat Completions
gpt-4o-search-preview.description: GPT-4o Search Preview is a specialized model trained to understand and execute web search queries with the Chat Completions API. In addition to token fees, web search queries have a fee per tool call.

pricing.pricing_model: Token-based + per-tool-call for search

gpt-4o-mini-search-preview.summary: Fast, affordable small model for web search
gpt-4o-mini-search-preview.description: GPT-4o mini Search Preview is a specialized model trained to understand and execute web search queries with the Chat Completions API. In addition to token fees, web search queries have a fee per tool call.

pricing.pricing_model: Token-based + per-tool-call for search

computer-use-preview.summary: Specialized model for computer use tool
computer-use-preview.description: The computer-use-preview model is a specialized model for the computer use tool. It is trained to understand and execute computer tasks. This model is only usable in the Responses API.

pricing.pricing_model: Token-based + per-tool-call

babbage-002.summary: Replacement for the GPT-3 ada and babbage base models
babbage-002.description: GPT base models can understand and generate natural language or code but are not trained with instruction following. These models are made to be replacements for our original GPT-3 base models and use the legacy Completions API. Most customers should use GPT-3.5 or GPT-4.

pricing.pricing_model: Token-based

davinci-002.summary: Replacement for the GPT-3 curie and davinci base models
davinci-002.description: GPT base models can understand and generate natural language or code but are not trained with instruction following. These models are made to be replacements for our original GPT-3 base models and use the legacy Completions API. Most customers should use GPT-3.5 or GPT-4.
